== Related concepts ==

The related concept of [[dieoff]] in [[population biology]] refers to the precipitous drop in any population once it has [[overgrazing|overgrazed]] its environment to the point where it is simply no longer viable as a population.  This usually occurs far before a full-spectrum ecocide, however, as few organisms consume a wide range of foods, nor directly transform (or "[[terraform]]") [[ecoregion]]s simply to serve their own purposes.  Thus total [[extinction]] of all life seems unlikely.

